reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Lots of stuff, sturdy case
reviews.reviewText: Got this for my teenage nephew for his hiking pack. He loved how much stuff was in it and the sturdy case it came in. He is really excited to finally have a decent first aide kit!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 20, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good for the price
reviews.reviewText: The kit is compact so I can put it in my small hiking backpack that I use on day trips. It has a lot of items in it to include a multi tool with can opener. I think I'll be better prepared in case of any emergency when I'm hiking

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice first aid kit for hiking
reviews.reviewText: I threw this in my hiking backpack and feel confident I can handle most small situations with this kit.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 25, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best little kit Ever
reviews.reviewText: Love this I am a travel agent that travels with her clients. I bought this to go to Costa Rica and it was the best thing ever it had everything I could have even imagined. We even tried out the fishing line. Got a couple of nibbles but didn't catch anything but not surprised I can't catch anything with a pole. It has a compass that we used while hiking. Not big at all but a little heavy as it has a ton of stuff in it. But worth a little weight.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 8, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Not too bad
reviews.reviewText: The overall quality of this kit decent. The knife is sharpish, there are plenty of antiseptic wipes and alcohol pads, the multi tool has decent weight (the quality of it will be tested this weekend). The issues I have with this kit is that the fish hook and line doesn’t look quality and the hooks came with nothing protecting them so if you’re not careful, you might get pricked. The pocket chainsaw looks a little thin but let’s see how well that works.**will update as I use what’s in the kit**

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 15, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great quality and alot of stuff
reviews.reviewText: I love this kit and you get alot for the price. Came in handy today because my bf cut the crap out of his hand and i used the fabric and gauze. And they actually include alot of bandaids

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 3, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great compact Med kit for camping trips and hiking
reviews.reviewText: Very organized Compact and full of all Essentials needed from Miner scrapes and bruises to cuts and lacerations that not too deep safe for Staples but will get you to the nearest place to catch an ambulance to the hospital with serious injuries this med kit will keep you alive until you can get to a hospital best part of my bug out bag is having one of these first aid kits because you always get some bumps and bruises and maybe some serious Cuts while out in the wilderness very pleased with this item and it came faster and better than described for delivery
